ICS 156: Networking Lab 3.2.2 Operation of Routers (2/2) nRouting mechanism: the action of looking an address up in a table and deciding what to do with the IP datagram -> Performed by IP nRouting policy: the actual algorithms that are use to make routing calculations and fill the routing table with forwarding entries -> Performed by a routing daemon